(The direction can be stated as \theta = 31^\circ \textrm{N of W} or as \phi = 60^\circ\textrm{W of N}.) will use this calculation to find the acceleration.

components: Given the mass and the components of the net force, we can calculate the acceleration.
\vec a =\frac{\vec F_\mathrm{net}}{m} = \frac{4.0\unit{N} \ihat + 5.0\unit{N} \jhat}{2.0\unit{kg}} = 2.0\unitfrac{m}{s^2} \ihat + 2.5\unitfrac{m}{s^2} \jhat
