The first thing we should do is notice what information is given to us and make sure that everything is in consistent units.  I will convert everything to SI units and find the weight of each mass:

                                         F_{g1} & = m_1 g & = (0.010 \unit{kg})(9.81\unitfrac{m}{s^2}) & = 0.0\sig{98}{1}{N}
